paper_abstract: A computer calculation with M a g m a shows that there is no extremal self-dual binary code C of length 72 whose automorphism group contains the symmetric group of degree 3, the alternating group of degree 4 or the dihedral group of order 8. Combining this with the known results in the literature one obtains that Aut(C) has order at most 5 or is isomorphic to the elementary abelian group of order 8.
paper_title: THE AUTOMORPHISM GROUP OF A SELF-DUAL [72,36,16] CODE DOES NOT CONTAIN S-3, A(4) OR D-8
